content: So good I bought the physical game as well.
It is fun. I wish the app didn't bug you to rate the app every time you look at the shipping for consume menu.
Fantastic implementation of a great game. Almost never crashes!

I'm hooked. I played the physical game just once, and was in love with it. This is an excellent digital adoption. Responsive with crisp graphics. The AI is sharp with no evidence of "cheating." I haven't yet played multiplayer. I own on Steam and Google. Really hoping for expansions.
Best app I've played in a long time. Bought the physical boardgame because of this app. Great job on this one!
A great replica of the physical game!
Fantastic layout for a really good game. The core board game design is not as solid as Race, but I've still played an insane amount of it.
Nice visuals, good AI but often quits online games ...

I've owned the physical copy since the game came out. It still hits the table more often than not. During covid times its hard to get together with friends to play games. This is absolutely awesome. Well done.

I have the physical game as well, and this version replicates the gameplay faithfully. The game streamlines the process of assigning dice very well and is very addictive. The AI is very good. I have yet to beat the medium AI. Awesome game!
Simply, the best. Excited for the Ambition expansion tho.
Fun dice strategy
I love this game. I can't wait for the expansion

I love the game, love the app, but the bugs do drive me up the wall sometimes. Constantly having to restart the app, app crashing occasionally. Really really really great game, all around. Mentioned the bugs because i hope they get fixed üòÅ
The app looks nice but this game is more luck than strategy. You can win by placing worlds as fast as you can and hitting auto button. Got bored as soon as I learned how to play. Not worth 10 bucks.
I find it challenging to beat in a 3p expert mode. Great mechanics and ease of use. It's fun to grab a quick game on your phone.
Great game, game stopping bugs have been fixed. And the hard AIs play a tough game!
Plays just like the actual dice game. No bugs or crashes after about 40 games. Very happy with this purchase.
Very well made implementation. I'm excited to get the expansion when it comes out!
Fantastic game. Really great way to learn the mechanics. Tap inaccuracy on my s10+ occasionally makes the game frustrating to play.
Flawless implementation of an incredible game.
If you love the board game, this is a faithful version with a great UI. Great app!

A great strategy game. I think the price is a bit steep but I'm happy to support. I would start with race for the galaxy if you are unfamiliar with these games as the iconography to understand what's happening has a bit of a learning curve. Excellent AI again. Would like to see a choice of starting tiles.
Amazing work done on the UI! It's a pretty complex game with lots of information through it's still a breeze to play on a mobile phone. Kudos to the devs.

Great implementation - worthy of five stars, but with some reservations. The touch accuracy seems a bit off on my Pixel4XL - meaning I'm missing the die I need to move often enough to be a bit annoying. Not sure if many other android devices have the 'swipe from edge' feature - but it means you'll accidentally exit the app or pull up the bottom drawer often. This can be turned off but still. A bit frustrating. Also - (and this is selfish) this is a great game, but it REALLY needs the expansion to come alive in terms of choice and variety. Looking forward to the release!
Once you wrap your head around the rule dynamics, Roll for the Galaxy is a deeply rewarding strategy game that's immensely satisfying to play üëç

Plays roll for the galaxy well, has good graphics, and decent lack of battery usage. I wish there were a few house rules options; the biggest 2 I think of is the ability to change the tile requirements for ending the game away from 12 and the ability to pick from 2 random start tiles.
Wonderful implementation of the game. Very happy with my purchase.
Big fan. Slightly buggy with backgrounding on my pixel 3. Looking forward to the expansions!

Interface easy enough to understand. It's always going to be difficult cramming everything on to a small phone screen but it works well, it runs smoothly and I haven't had any issues. The game itself is good fun and addictive. AIs are of reasonable strength
Great game, waiting on the expansion.
Great app. Good port from the physical game but still buggy .
Very good digital version of one of my favorite games. A bit buggy sometimes but that all comes with new games. A simple restart fixes it.
Excellent replayability, strong AI, very clean implementation of the original board game!
Great implementation of a really fun board game.
Great game.
A faithful adaptation of a very good game. Crucially, the auto button populates things extremely logically, and saves a huge amount of time on what could have been tedious dragging.
A great implementation of a great boardgame.
Great adaptation of the boardgame! I love how quick it can play while still having that fun thinky depth. Love it!

Bought this as a beta (which required the full ¬£10 purchase) with the intention to play with friends online. It looks nifty but was riddled with bugs (it sounds like many still exist) and games just took too long (35 minutes if trying to play quickly), but had potential if online play were made quicker and the kinks ironed out. After all, the Race for the Galaxy app is incredibly well-made and probably my all-time favourite. Unfortunately, it appears none of this feedback was taken onboard and it just makes every game a drawn out, frustrating experience that has even killed any enthusiasm I had for the physical version (which I can't even play due to COVID-19). Anyway, my friends all got refunds while mine was refused, so here I am with a ¬£10 app I'll never use.

Great interface design, nice and uncluttered. I've got the actual dice version of the game, plus one of the expansions, so used to the mechanics of the game. The AI plays well too. Big fan of Temple games' ports of Race/Shards and now Roll, keep it up guys and let's see the expansions soon!

Great adaptation of the dice rolling game. I play mainly against AI, that's all I need and it does it well. Love it. Hope the expansions are being done as well. Goes to show you that paying ten bucks for a decent game is far better than any of the so called free-to-play games that are actually pay-to-win. Awesome!
Good adaptation of the board game with some bugs that change gameplay
We need a live multiplayer please. No wait to play moves or have it both ways so it's a choice. Nice game. It's not to big of learning curve. I enjoy it. Thank you.
Good adaptation of the game, but it murders battery life - 20 minutes of play ate 45% of my battery today.

I like this app a lot, and I've been a long-time player of the game. There's only one problem with the UI -- any time you're dragging a tile around, the tile is always aligned so that your finger covers up the descriptive text for the tile, and there's nothing you can do about it.
Dope. Smooth UI
Fantastic game.
Great successor of Race for the Galaxy. One of best paced card games, and one of two best dice deck builders alongside Quarriors.

Great implementation of the game, very smooth and visually great. UI could use another pass as touches sometimes feel inaccurate and knowing who I'm playing at all times would be helpful to keep games organized. None of this detracts from a perfect mobile implementation.
An excellent port of a fun board game
Good implementation
Great implementation of board game!
Well done. translated very well from the board game. Animations are smooth and game progresses well!
Smooth game play and good AI opponents
Will rate 5 when expansion will be out. Sometimes the touch control will be slightly up to where my finger is.
One of my favorite games recreated by an amazing developer.
Interface is very goods. Plays like the original game. Lots of fun.
Excellent game. Great App.
Well made and very fun! Worth the price especially if you already like engine-building games.
